I haven't heard that about mend, but I'm doubting it.  Mend works like LoH but just less of a heal.  There would be no reason to make it not work when full HP.

Mend will fail, and fail a LOT until you reach 100 skill.  After that it will work quite a bit, with just a few fails.  My monk, when she was in her low 30s, had about a 98% success rate with it.

Hit it every time it ungrays...unless you are solo'ing, in which you don't want to do that and get a critical failure (it hurts you).  Once you have it capped for your level, which you won't, you can stop hitting it.

I wish I could tell you more on the special attacks, but I've forgotten almost everything I knew about my monk...I stopped playing her ages ago, and deleted her shortly after LDoN to make her into a cleric.

