Here is an FDPractice macro I used when fighting to practice FD - your skill will go up quick.  Now here is the kicker - As a Monk, if you are not the Main Tank.. You do not want Aggro - it makes your Healers job harder.  Now that my FD is close to maxed I dont use it much to practice but I use it to drop aggro in groups.  It works well and helps me to keep Aggro on the MT (Main Tank).

/attack off
/doability # (the number assigned to fd)
/stand
/attack on

You get aggro - hit this and aggro will (90% of the time) go back to MT.

