It's not that hard to just re-engage auto-attack after using your "evade" (that's what I would call it) macro.  Hell, every second your late in re-engaging auto-attack is less aggro you're building up (granted, less DPS, too).

I had more macros on my monk than any other character.  I had combined skill macros to hit while just chatting with friends.  I had macros to use while travelling to work on skills.  Monks just have so many damn clickable skills to work on. :)

